RE: Overcoming the fear of death Fearing death. Can't say I haven't thought about it. You wouldn't be human if it didn't run across your mind. Now, don't think I'm being funny or mocking because I'm not... What did you not fear before you were born, that you fear after your death. You didn't exist with fear before and you won't when you cease to exist... it's possible your fear might be more of dying rather than being just nonexistent.
Might not be what you are looking for. Maybe just thinking about how you were before you were born might help even out your angst. I think in the end, I just feel like I'm a secular person who has a skeptical eye toward any extraordinary claim, carefully examining any extraordinary evidence before jumping to conclusions. ~ Eric ~ My friend ... who figured it out.
