RE: Overcoming the fear of death (04-02-2013 04:59 PM)Vosur Wrote: ...I simply have no idea how I should handle this paralyzing fear.
hmmmm, I would suggest that being prepared for an untimely death helps. Making amends with estranged family, enemies etc. I have life insurance. Not so much as to tempt the mrs with but enough to pay things off if I'm suddenly gone. I also feel like I've lived a full life. I've done a lot of things that I wanted to do and enjoyed doing and feel content that I've made the most of my life and it has been great!
Perhaps you need a bucket list? You know, do some shit that you can always look back on and say -I did that just because and it was crazy but worth it.
